article.headline: Tennessee Tech 63, Murray St. 52
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Belton Rivers scored 17 points and Tennessee Tech pulled away in the second half for a 63-52 win Tuesday night over Murray State. Tennessee Tech (11-9, 7-4 Ohio Valley Conference) shot just 33.9 percent but it was enough to win its fifth straight game. Murray State (8-11, 6-5) didn't shoot much better, 36.2 percent, and scored 10 fewer points at the free throw line. The Golden Eagles made 18-of-23 to Murray's 8-of-12. After a 28-28 tie at halftime, Tech led the rest of the way, opening up a 46-34 lead on a 3-pointer by Rivers with 11:06 left. The Racers got as close as 52-46 with 5:43 left, but the Golden Eagles stretched the lead to 11, 59-48, on two free throws by Anthony Fisher with 2:07 remaining. Fisher finished with 12 points and a team-high eight rebounds. Amadi McKenzie scored 12 on 5-of-7 shooting, and reserve Francis Kabore scored 10. Tyler Holoway scored 14 for Murray and Bruce Carter had 11 points and a game-high nine rebounds.
